  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed communications hub, by reason of its design, scale, siting, illumination and creation of additional street clutter, would harm the appearance of the surrounding townscape, Old Uxbridge / Windsor Street Conservation Area and the settings of the nearby Grade II listed buildings. The proposal is therefore contrary to Policies BE1 and HE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One - Strategic Policies (2012), Policies DMHB 1, 3, 4, 11, 12, 13A, 15 and 21 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part Two - Development Management Policies (2020), Policies HC1, D3, D5, D8 and T2 of The London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021).",
    "The proposed communications hub, by reason of its design, scale and siting would result in obstructions to sight lines for public realm users having an adverse impact on perceived safety and increased risk of crime and public safety implications, contrary to Policy BE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One (2012), Policy DMHB 15 of the  Hillingdon Local Plan: Part Two - Development Management Policies (2020), Policy D3 of the London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021).",
    "The decision to REFUSE planning permission has been taken having regard to all relevant planning legislation, regulations, guidance, circulars and Council policies, including The Human Rights Act (1998) (HRA 1998) which makes it unlawful for the Council to act incompatibly with Convention rights, specifically Article 6 (right to a fair hearing); Article 8 (right to respect for private and family life); Article 1 of the First Protocol (protection of property) and Article 14 (prohibition of discrimination).",
    "The decision to REFUSE planning permission has been taken having regard to the policies and proposals in the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 1 (2012) and Part 2 (2020) set out below, including Supplementary Planning Guidance, and to all relevant material considerations, including The London Plan (2021) and National Guidance."
  ],
